        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 4:02PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 402 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Masseyville, or 8 miles southeast of Chickasaw State Forest, moving
east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Forty Forks, Hornsby, New Lawton, Martin Camp, Rose Creek, Selmer,
Good Hope, Pine Top, Bethel Springs, Finger, Masseyville, Woodville,
Old Lawton, McNairy, Silerton, Hickory Corners, Robertson, Purdy,
Enville, and Stantonville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM CDT for
west Tennessee.</instruction>
